### Makerkit Integration

This project uses [MakerKit](https://makerkit.dev) (Teams license) as its SaaS framework foundation.

**MCP Tools Available:**
- `mcp__makerkit__*` - Built-in Makerkit tools (components, scripts, database, PRDs, migrations)
- `mcp__makerkit-docs__*` - Makerkit documentation search and retrieval

**Key Makerkit MCP Tools:**
- `mcp__makerkit__get_components` - List all UI components with metadata
- `mcp__makerkit__components_search` - Search components by keyword
- `mcp__makerkit__get_scripts` - List available pnpm scripts
- `mcp__makerkit__run_checks` - Run code quality checks (typecheck, lint, format)
- `mcp__makerkit__get_database_resources` - Database schema introspection
- `mcp__makerkit__get_migrations` / `create_migration` / `diff_migrations` - Migration management
- `mcp__makerkit__prd_manager` - PRD management with user stories
- `mcp__makerkit__deps_upgrade_advisor` - Dependency upgrade recommendations
- `mcp__makerkit-docs__makerkit_docs_search` - Search Makerkit documentation
- `mcp__makerkit-docs__makerkit_docs_read` - Read specific doc files

**Generated Docs Location:** `.claude-framework/vendor/makerkit/docs-generated/` (33 files, ~188K words)

**Usage Guidelines:**
- ALWAYS check `mcp__makerkit__get_components` before creating custom UI components
- ALWAYS run `mcp__makerkit__run_checks` after major changes
- Use `mcp__makerkit-docs__makerkit_docs_search` to find Makerkit patterns before implementing
- Follow Makerkit conventions for routing, layouts, and data fetching
- MakerKit is a pattern reference, NOT a runtime dependency -- study patterns via MCP, build with project UI library
<!-- MAKERKIT-SECTION-END -->
